HOW TO CHOOSE A LONDON DIGITAL AGENCY — Meridian Digital Ltd

An 18-page buyer's guide written for the person across the table from us. We've sat through enough pitches from the other side to know exactly which questions separate a great London agency from a budget-burner. The guide opens with the diagnostic most buyers skip: defining the actual problem before shortlisting, and deciding whether the right answer is in-house, a boutique agency, a larger network shop, or a trusted freelancer.

The middle of the guide is our 22-point agency scorecard — the criteria we'd use if we were hiring us — covering commercial model transparency, reporting credibility, team seniority on your actual account (not the pitch), case-study verifiability, contract flexibility, and the cultural signals that predict long-term fit. Each criterion has a red-flag column so you can tell quickly which agencies are likely to disappoint.

The final third contains templates you can use today: a fill-in-the-blanks RFP to send to every shortlisted agency, a reference-check script with the exact questions to ask past clients, and a kickoff checklist for the agency you eventually pick — designed to front-load the hardest conversations so the relationship starts with clarity instead of goodwill-draining friction.
